Author: DanielBMarkham
Content: Interested in any comments about this article -- I thought about submitting it to a client who is really gung-ho on XP and Agile, but I'm not sure if I'm making any sense or if it would tick them off. Feedback appreciated.

Author: Xichekolas
Content:
Don't you think it's a waste of time to pre-plan your holiday wishes to be so politically correct? You could wish me a Happy Kwanzaa and I'd get the idea that you wanted to wish me well for whatever holiday I choose to celebrate... I wouldn't immediately be offended because you didn't know which 'holiday reference' I preferred to hear.

So uh... Happy Fourth of July!
